{
  "texts": [
    "At every point the meaning changes, and it is the person doing the meaning who changes it.",
    "This is why we call meaning a process of transposition.",
    "It is a cognitive process and a material process, making meaning in media (Kalantzis and Cope 2020: 47-63).Literacy is transpositional.",
    "Meanings must be remade as meanings-for-oneself become meanings for others, and the meanings of others become meanings for-oneself.",
    "Fig. 2: Participation in textual meaningThis throws into question traditional tests of reading, forced into select response assessments."
  ]
}